Lebanon needs emergency international relief 
@UNAction
 @antonioguterres

Horrific day! All our thoughts go to 
@RedCrossLebanon
 paramedics & volunteers who have been evacuating the injured by #LebanonExplosion. Proud of each & everyone of you. We stand with you & with the Lebanese people during this difficult time. 
@IFRC_MENA
 allocated funds in support

It was a tough night here in #Beirut . We took care of more than 500 injured 
@LAUMCRH
 . There were casualties. The ED looked like a scene in a war movie, a horrible one... Our hospital is destroyed. It is a sad night... Tomorrow should be a better day...

Supporting 
@RedCrossLebanon
 now to respond to the tragic massive explosion in Beirut. Red Cross ambulances on the scene and situation is fluid. 
@IFRC_MENA

I think it is time for the international community to provide Lebanon with urgent assistance. Political considerations are no longer valid.
